HEADWORD: Buffel duck
<hw>Buf"fel duck</hw> <pr>(b⟦ucr⟧f"f⟦ecr⟧l d⟦ucr⟧k`)</pr>. <ety>[See
<er>Buffalo</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small duck
(<spn>Charitonetta albeola</spn>); the spirit duck, or butterball. The
head of the male is covered with numerous elongated feathers, and thus
appears large. Called also <altname>bufflehead</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buffer</ent>⟦br⟧
